# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Trivy CVE ignore list — each entry MUST include a clear reason and an
# expiration date so we re-evaluate periodically.
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# CVE-2025-59250 — Microsoft JDBC Driver for SQL Server improper input
# validation. Microsoft's official fixed-version list:
#   10.2.4.jre11, 11.2.4.jre11, 12.2.1.jre11, 12.6.5.jre11,
#   12.8.2.jre11, 12.10.2.jre11, 13.2.1.jre11
# We ship 12.10.2.jre11, which IS in the fixed list. Trivy reads the
# JAR's pom.properties as "12.10.2" (without the .jre11 build suffix) and
# matches that against an unfixed entry — a known Trivy bug with
# Microsoft's jre-suffix versioning.
# Verify manually: unzip -p engine.jar META-INF/maven/com.microsoft.sqlserver/mssql-jdbc/pom.properties
# Revisit: 2026-12-31  (drop when Trivy fixes the version comparator,
# or when we bump to mssql-jdbc 13.x major)
CVE-2025-59250
